item.title: L.e. add a quote by Marisa de los Santos
item.description: "Jimmy Stewart is always and indisputably the best man in the world, unless Cary Grant should happen to show up." -- Marisa de los Santos

item.title: L.e. add a quote by Sir William Osler
item.description: "One of the first duties of the physician is to educate the masses not to take medicine." -- Sir William Osler

item.title: L.e. add a quote by sir william osler
item.description: "It is astonishing with how little reading a doctor can practice medicine, but is not astonishing how badly he may do it." -- sir william osler

item.title: L.e. add a quote by william faulkner
item.description: "You should approach Joyce's Ulysses as the illiterate Baptist preacher approaches the Old Testament: with faith." -- william faulkner

item.title: L.e. add a quote by Marisa de los Santos
item.description: "We talked and talked and talked. Maybe love comes in at the eyes, but not nearly as much as it comes in at the ears, at least in my experience. As we talked, lights flicked on inside my head; by the end of the night I was a planterium." -- Marisa de los Santos
